@Jason, with any approvals/feedback items where the maintainer isn't changing the issue themselves, please reference how/where the feedback/approval was obtained.

Ideally, the maintainer can/should set these flags themselves, which avoids ambiguities and potential conflicts ("no, i didnt really/explicitly/officially say this or that".

Was there an issue for the MAINTAINER change request and approval? If so, reference that as a/the blocking issue for these changes so that the audit trail can be followed easily
